5â€“9. Write the Python Program (With Variables, Input & Comments)
Final Code (Fully Commented)
# Import datetime module to get today's date
import datetime

# Ask user to enter their name
name = input("Enter your name: ")

# Ask user to enter their internship role
role = input("Enter your internship role: ")

# Get today's date
today_date = datetime.date.today()

# Print the details
print("\n--- Intern Details ---")
print("Name:", name)
print("Internship Role:", role)
print("Today's Date:", today_date)

6. Why Variables Are Used

name â†’ stores user's name

role â†’ stores internship role

today_date â†’ stores current date

âœ… This avoids hardcoding values and makes the program reusable.

